    ) VALUES (1416768, 'Amprenavir', 'Drospirenone', 'Major', 'Coadministration with potent inhibitors of CYP450 3A4 may significantly increase the plasma concentrations of drospirenone which is primarily metabolized by the isoenzyme. High exposure to drospirenone may potentiate the risk hyperkalemia. Drospirenone has antimineralocorticoid activity and can induce hyperkalemia in susceptible patients.', NULL, 'Caution and close clinical monitoring are recommended, especially in patients requiring long-term use and those at increased risk for hyperkalemia (e.', NULL, 'Caution and close clinical monitoring are recommended, especially in patients requiring long-term use and those at increased risk for hyperkalemia (e.g., patients with renal impairment, those receiving potassium-sparing medications). Because of the risk for hyperkalemia, concomitant use with certain CYP450 3A4 inhibitors such as boceprevir or atazanavir boosted with cobicistat, is considered contraindicated by the manufacturers. Consider checking potassium levels during the first treatment cycle of concomitant drospirenone use and then periodically as indicated.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317476);
